Package: comptoxtools
Title: CompTox Chemical Data Retrieval, ToxPrint Chemotype Analysis, and
    UMAP Visualisation
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R:
    person("First", "Last", , "first.last@example.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: A toolkit for cheminformatics workflows centred on the EPA
    CompTox ecosystem. Provides functions to query the CompTox Chemical
    Dashboard API for chemical identity (DTXSID, CAS-RN, SMILES, preferred
    name), physico-chemical property data, and structure images. Includes
    a suite of ToxPrint chemotype analysis tools: dataset-level proportion
    calculations, per-chemical chemotype counts, and Fisher's exact test
    enrichment analyses (with confusion-matrix metrics) for individual
    chemotypes, pairwise or triplet combinations, and multiple assays in
    parallel — all operating on the bundled ToxPrint v2.0 (r711) naming
    hierarchy across five levels of specificity. Also provides a UMAP
    dimensionality-reduction pipeline (projection, tidy layout, and
    ggplot2 visualisation) and a utility to recover CAS registry numbers
    that Excel has corrupted by auto-formatting them as dates. Parallel
    execution is supported via 'furrr' and optional progress reporting via
    'progressr'.
